                             +        if (set.size() > MAX_PAGE_TREE_ENTRIES)                                                                                                                                    
                             +        {                                                                                                                                                                          
                             +            throw new IOException("Page tree exceeds maximum allowed entries: " + set.size());                                                                                     
                             +        }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                      // check for kids                                                                                                                                                          
                                      COSArray kidsArray = pagesDict.getCOSArray(COSName.KIDS);                                                                                                                  
                                      int numberOfPages = 0;

                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             The fuzzing session terminated with an ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout message. In other words, the libFuzzer run exceeded its allotted execution time without                          
                             completing, and was aborted by the fuzzer framework.                                                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Issue description                                                                                                                                                                 
                               During automated fuzz testing, libFuzzer reported a timeout. This indicates that one or more inputs caused the harness or the code under test to run longer than                  
                             the configured time limit, prompting libFuzzer to halt execution.                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Vulnerability type                                                                                                                                                                
                               No specific vulnerability type (e.g., memory corruption, integer overflow) is explicitly mentioned in the error. The timeout alone does not identify a security                   
                             flaw, but it may hint at hangs, infinite loops, or performance bottlenecks.                                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Key observations and findings                                                                                                                                                     
                                The timeout originates in the fuzzers runtime rather than in the harness logic itself.                                                                                         
                                There is no stack trace or crash log; the failure mode is purely a time-based abort.                                                                                            
                                The harness serves only as an entry pointits role is to feed inputs to the target code.                                                                                        
                                Timeout occurrences may be intermittent or reproducible on particular inputs, but the report does not specify which.                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Areas for investigation                                                                                                                                                           
                               1. Fuzz harness entry point                                                                                                                                                       
                                   Review how inputs are fed into the target functions and whether the harness imposes any unintended delays.                                                                   
                               2. Target code paths                                                                                                                                                              
                                   Identify functions or modules that perform extensive computation, recursive calls, or blocking I/O.                                                                          
                                   Examine loops, state machines, or algorithms that could fail to terminate under certain inputs.                                                                              
                               3. Performance-critical components                                                                                                                                                
                                   Check for known hotspots in parsing routines, cryptographic operations, or large data structure manipulations.                                                               
                               4. Fuzzer configuration                                                                                                                                                           
                                   Verify the timeout threshold and any related flags (e.g., `-timeout`, `-rss_limit_mb`).                                                                                      
                                   Confirm that the environment (CPU, memory) matches expected testing conditions.                                                                                              
                               5. Coverage and instrumentation                                                                                                                                                   
                                   Analyze coverage reports to see if the fuzzer is stuck exploring the same code region.                                                                                       
                                   Ensure sanitizer or instrumentation overhead is not inadvertently inflating execution time.                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             By examining the harness, the invoked code paths, and the fuzzer settings, one can gain a holistic view of why the libFuzzer session timed out and determine                        
                             whether the underlying code exhibits problematic behavior under fuzz-driven inputs.                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                                                                                                
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                                                                                                                      
                             <issue>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </issue>

                             25:/**

                             29: * @author Ben Litchfield                                                                                                                                                        
                             30: * @author Tilman Hausherr                                                                                                                                                       
                             31: */                                                                                                                                                                              
                             32:final class RunLengthDecodeFilter extends Filter                                                                                                                                 
                             33:{                                                                                                                                                                                
                             34:    private static final int RUN_LENGTH_EOD = 128;                                                                                                                               
                             35:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             36:    @Override                                                                                                                                                                    
                             37:    public DecodeResult decode(InputStream encoded, OutputStream decoded,                                                                                                        
                             38:                                         COSDictionary parameters, int index) throws IOException                                                                                 
                             39:    {                                                                                                                                                                            
                             40:        int dupAmount;                                                                                                                                                           
                             41:        byte[] buffer = new byte[128];                                                                                                                                           
                             42:        while ((dupAmount = encoded.read()) != -1 && dupAmount != RUN_LENGTH_EOD)                                                                                                
                             43:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             44:            if (dupAmount <= 127)                                                                                                                                                
                             45:            {                                                                                                                                                                    
                             46:                int amountToCopy = dupAmount + 1;                                                                                                                                
                             47:                int compressedRead;                                                                                                                                              
                             48:                while (amountToCopy > 0)                                                                                                                                         
                             49:                {                                                                                                                                                                
                             50:                    compressedRead = encoded.read(buffer, 0, amountToCopy);                                                                                                      
                             51:                    // EOF reached?                                                                                                                                              
                             52:                    if (compressedRead == -1)                                                                                                                                    
                             53:                    {                                                                                                                                                            
                             54:                        break;                                                                                                                                                   
                             55:                    }                                                                                                                                                            
                             56:                    decoded.write(buffer, 0, compressedRead);                                                                                                                    
                             57:                    amountToCopy -= compressedRead;                                                                                                                              
                             58:                }                                                                                                                                                                
                             59:            }                                                                                                                                                                    
                             60:            else                                                                                                                                                                 
                             61:            {                                                                                                                                                                    
                             62:                int dupByte = encoded.read();                                                                                                                                    
                             63:                // EOF reached?                                                                                                                                                  
                             64:                if (dupByte == -1)                                                                                                                                               
                             65:                {                                                                                                                                                                
                             66:                    break;                                                                                                                                                       
                             67:                }                                                                                                                                                                
                             68:                for (int i = 0; i < 257 - dupAmount; i++)                                                                                                                        
                             69:                {                                                                                                                                                                
                             70:                    decoded.write(dupByte);                                                                                                                                      
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFParser.java:115-125                                                                                                             
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             115:        if (isLenient() && !root.containsKey(COSName.TYPE))                                                                                                                     
                             116:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             117:            root.setItem(COSName.TYPE, COSName.CATALOG);                                                                                                                        
                             118:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             119:        // check pages dictionaries                                                                                                                                             
                             120:        checkPages(root);

                             122:        initialParseDone = true;
