                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BaseParser.java:1319-1343                                                                                                          
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1319:    protected void skipSpaces() throws IOException                                                                                                                             
                             1320:    {                                                                                                                                                                          
                             1321:        int c = source.read();                                                                                                                                                 
                             1322:        // 37 is the % character, a comment                                                                                                                                    
                             1323:        while( isWhitespace(c) || c == 37)                                                                                                                                     
                             1324:        {                                                                                                                                                                      
                             1325:            if ( c == 37 )                                                                                                                                                     
                             1326:            {                                                                                                                                                                  
                             1327:                // skip past the comment section                                                                                                                               
                             1328:                c = source.read();                                                                                                                                             
                             1329:                while(!isEOL(c) && c != -1)                                                                                                                                    
                             1330:                {                                                                                                                                                              
                             1331:                    c = source.read();                                                                                                                                         
                             1332:                }                                                                                                                                                              
                             1333:            }                                                                                                                                                                  
                             1334:            else                                                                                                                                                               
                             1335:            {                                                                                                                                                                  
                             1336:                c = source.read();                                                                                                                                             
                             1337:            }                                                                                                                                                                  
                             1338:        }                                                                                                                                                                      
                             1339:        if (c != -1)                                                                                                                                                           
                             1340:        {                                                                                                                                                                      
                             1341:            source.rewind(1);                                                                                                                                                  
                             1342:        }                                                                                                                                                                      
                             1343:    }                                                                                                                                                                          
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/COSParser.java:938-1010                                                                                                            
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             938:    protected void checkPages(COSDictionary root) throws IOException                                                                                                            
                             939:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             940:        if (trailerWasRebuild)                                                                                                                                                  
                             941:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             942:            // check if all page objects are dereferenced                                                                                                                       
                             943:            COSDictionary pages = root.getCOSDictionary(COSName.PAGES);                                                                                                         
                             944:            if (pages != null)                                                                                                                                                  
                             945:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             946:                checkPagesDictionary(pages, new HashSet<>());                                                                                                                   
                             947:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             948:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             949:        if (root.getCOSDictionary(COSName.PAGES) == null)                                                                                                                       
                             950:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             951:            throw new IOException("Page tree root must be a dictionary");                                                                                                       
                             952:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             953:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             954:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             955:    private int checkPagesDictionary(COSDictionary pagesDict, Set<COSObject> set)                                                                                               
                             956:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             957:        // check for kids                                                                                                                                                       
                             958:        COSArray kidsArray = pagesDict.getCOSArray(COSName.KIDS);                                                                                                               
                             959:        int numberOfPages = 0;                                                                                                                                                  
                             960:        if (kidsArray != null)                                                                                                                                                  
                             961:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             962:            List<? extends COSBase> kidsList = kidsArray.toList();                                                                                                              
                             963:            for (COSBase kid : kidsList)                                                                                                                                        
                             964:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             965:                if (!(kid instanceof COSObject) || set.contains((COSObject) kid))                                                                                               
                             966:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             967:                    kidsArray.remove(kid);                                                                                                                                      
                             968:                    continue;                                                                                                                                                   
                             969:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             970:                COSObject kidObject = (COSObject) kid;                                                                                                                          
                             971:                COSBase kidBaseobject = kidObject.getObject();                                                                                                                  
                             972:                // object wasn't dereferenced -> remove it                                                                                                                      
                             973:                if (kidBaseobject == null || kidBaseobject.equals(COSNull.NULL))                                                                                                
                             974:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             975:                    LOG.warn("Removed null object {} from pages dictionary", kid);                                                                                              
                             976:                    kidsArray.remove(kid);                                                                                                                                      
                             977:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             978:                else if (kidBaseobject instanceof COSDictionary)                                                                                                                
                             979:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             980:                    COSDictionary kidDictionary = (COSDictionary) kidBaseobject;                                                                                                
                             981:                    COSName type = kidDictionary.getCOSName(COSName.TYPE);                                                                                                      
                             982:                    if (COSName.PAGES.equals(type))                                                                                                                             
                             983:                    {                                                                                                                                                           
                             984:                        // process nested pages dictionaries                                                                                                                    
                             985:                        set.add(kidObject);                                                                                                                                     
                             986:                        numberOfPages += checkPagesDictionary(kidDictionary, set);                                                                                              
                             987:                    }                                                                                                                                                           
                             988:                    else if (COSName.PAGE.equals(type))                                                                                                                         
                             989:                    {                                                                                                                                                           
                             990:                        // count pages                                                                                                                                          
                             991:                        numberOfPages++;                                                                                                                                        
                             992:                    }                                                                                                                                                           
                             993:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             994:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             995:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             996:        // fix counter                                                                                                                                                          
                             997:        pagesDict.setInt(COSName.COUNT, numberOfPages);                                                                                                                         
                             998:        return numberOfPages;                                                                                                                                                   
                             999:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             1000:                                                                                                                                                                               
                             1001:    /**                                                                                                                                                                        
                             1002:     * Checks if the given string can be found at the current offset.                                                                                                          
                             1003:     *                                                                                                                                                                         
                             1004:     * @param string the bytes of the string to look for                                                                                                                       
                             1005:     * @return true if the bytes are in place, false if not                                                                                                                    
                             1006:     * @throws IOException if something went wrong                                                                                                                             
                             1007:     */                                                                                                                                                                        
                             1008:    private boolean isString(byte[] string) throws IOException                                                                                                                 
                             1009:    {                                                                                                                                                                          
                             1010:        boolean bytesMatching = true;                                                                                                                                          
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFObjectStreamParser.java:37-120                                                                                                  
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             37:public class PDFObjectStreamParser extends BaseParser                                                                                                                            
                             38:{                                                                                                                                                                                
                             39:    private final int numberOfObjects;                                                                                                                                           
                             40:    private final int firstObject;                                                                                                                                               
                             41:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             42:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             43:     * Constructor.                                                                                                                                                              
                             44:     *                                                                                                                                                                           
                             45:     * @param stream The stream to parse.                                                                                                                                        
                             46:     * @param document The document for the current parsing.                                                                                                                     
                             47:     * @throws IOException If there is an error initializing the stream.                                                                                                         
                             48:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             49:    public PDFObjectStreamParser(COSStream stream, COSDocument document) throws IOException                                                                                      
                             50:    {                                                                                                                                                                            
                             51:        super(stream.createView());                                                                                                                                              
                             52:        this.document = document;                                                                                                                                                
                             53:        // get mandatory number of objects                                                                                                                                       
                             54:        numberOfObjects = stream.getInt(COSName.N);                                                                                                                              
                             55:        if (numberOfObjects == -1)                                                                                                                                               
                             56:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             57:            throw new IOException("/N entry missing in object stream");                                                                                                          
                             58:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             59:        if (numberOfObjects < 0)                                                                                                                                                 
                             60:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             61:            throw new IOException("Illegal /N entry in object stream: " + numberOfObjects);                                                                                      
                             62:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             63:        // get mandatory stream offset of the first object                                                                                                                       
                             64:        firstObject = stream.getInt(COSName.FIRST);                                                                                                                              
                             65:        if (firstObject == -1)                                                                                                                                                   
                             66:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             67:            throw new IOException("/First entry missing in object stream");                                                                                                      
                             68:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             69:        if (firstObject < 0)                                                                                                                                                     
                             70:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             71:            throw new IOException("Illegal /First entry in object stream: " + firstObject);                                                                                      
                             72:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             73:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             74:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             75:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             76:     * Search for/parse the object with the given object number. The stream is closed after parsing the object with the                                                          
                             77:     * given number.                                                                                                                                                             
                             78:     *                                                                                                                                                                           
                             79:     * @param objectNumber the number of the object to b e parsed                                                                                                                
                             80:     * @return the parsed object or null if the object with the given number can't be found                                                                                      
                             81:     * @throws IOException if there is an error while parsing the stream                                                                                                         
                             82:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             83:    public COSBase parseObject(long objectNumber) throws IOException                                                                                                             
                             84:    {                                                                                                                                                                            
                             85:        COSBase streamObject = null;                                                                                                                                             
                             86:        try                                                                                                                                                                      
                             87:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             88:            Integer objectOffset = privateReadObjectNumbers().get(objectNumber);                                                                                                 
                             89:            if (objectOffset != null)                                                                                                                                            
                             90:            {                                                                                                                                                                    
                             91:                // jump to the offset of the first object                                                                                                                        
                             92:                long currentPosition = source.getPosition();                                                                                                                     
                             93:                if (firstObject > 0 && currentPosition < firstObject)                                                                                                            
                             94:                {                                                                                                                                                                
                             95:                    source.skip(firstObject - (int) currentPosition);                                                                                                            
                             96:                }                                                                                                                                                                
                             97:                // jump to the offset of the object to be parsed                                                                                                                 
                             98:                source.skip(objectOffset);                                                                                                                                       
                             99:                streamObject = parseDirObject();                                                                                                                                 
                             100:                if (streamObject != null)                                                                                                                                       
                             101:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             102:                    streamObject.setDirect(false);                                                                                                                              
                             103:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             104:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             105:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             106:        finally                                                                                                                                                                 
                             107:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             108:            source.close();                                                                                                                                                     
                             109:            document = null;                                                                                                                                                    
                             110:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             111:        return streamObject;                                                                                                                                                    
                             112:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             113:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             114:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             115:     * Parse all compressed objects. The stream is closed after parsing.                                                                                                        
                             116:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             117:     * @return a map containing all parsed objects using the object number as key                                                                                               
                             118:     * @throws IOException if there is an error while parsing the stream                                                                                                        
                             119:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             120:    public Map<COSObjectKey, COSBase> parseAllObjects() throws IOException                                                                                                      
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Overview of Root Causes                                                                                                                                                          
                                - PDFObjectStreamParser: unbounded loops driven by the `/N` entry (`numberOfObjects`) in an object stream. Malicious or fuzzed inputs can set `N` to extremely                   
                             large values, causing parse loops (in `privateReadObjectNumbers()`, `parseAllObjects()` and even `parseObject()`) to iterate excessively and trigger timeouts.                      
                                - checkPagesDictionary (via `checkPages`): deep or extremely large page-tree recursion when `trailerWasRebuild` is true. Although cycles are prevented by a                      
                             visited-set, a very large or deeply nested page tree will cost linear (or worse) time per node, again causing long hangs under fuzz inputs.                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Critical Logic to Preserve                                                                                                                                                       
                                - Correct parsing of valid object streams and page trees for well-formed PDFs.                                                                                                   
                                - Cycle-detection in page-tree traversal must remain.                                                                                                                            
                                - Correct exception semantics on malformed or truncated streams.                                                                                                                 
                                - No changes to harness, fuzzing logic, or external dependencies.                                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                A. Introduce Reasonable Upper Bounds on Fuzz-Driven Counts                                                                                                                       
                                - Define two static constants in `PDFObjectStreamParser` (or in a central `ParserConfig`):                                                                                       
                                     `MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS = 100_000`                                                                                                                                      
                                     `MAX_PAGE_TREE_ENTRIES = 100_000`                                                                                                                                          
                                - Rationale: these thresholds are high enough to handle legitimate PDFs while preventing pathological loops under fuzz.                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                B. Cap `numberOfObjects` in PDFObjectStreamParser                                                                                                                                
                                - In the constructor (after reading `numberOfObjects`):                                                                                                                          
                                     If `numberOfObjects > MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS`, throw `IOException("Object stream /N value too large")`.                                                                 
                                     This prevents building an enormous `privateReadObjectNumbers()` map or iterating millions of times.                                                                        
                                - In `parseAllObjects()` (before the loop):                                                                                                                                      
                                     Re-check `numberOfObjects`  `MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS`.                                                                                                                  
                                - In `privateReadObjectNumbers()`:                                                                                                                                               
                                     As it reads object numbers, keep a counter; if counter exceeds `MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS`, throw an `IOException`.                                                        
                                - This triage ensures no unbounded work even if the constructor was bypassed or the parser is invoked differently.                                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                C. Limit Page-Tree Traversal Depth/Size                                                                                                                                          
                                - In `COSParser.checkPagesDictionary(...)`:                                                                                                                                      
                                     Pass an additional counter or check the size of the visited-set (`set.size()`).                                                                                            
                                     If `set.size() > MAX_PAGE_TREE_ENTRIES`, abort traversal by throwing an `IOException("Page tree too large")`.                                                              
                                     Alternatively, return early and set the `/Count` entry to the pages counted so far.                                                                                        
                                - This caps total nodes visited and ensures the recursion cannot consume unbounded CPU.                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Implementation Steps                                                                                                                                                             
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                1. In `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/ParserConfig.java` (new file or existing config holder):                                                                 
                                   - Define:                                                                                                                                                                     
                                     ```java                                                                                                                                                                     
                                     public final class ParserConfig {                                                                                                                                           
                                         public static final int MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS = 100_000;                                                                                                            
                                         public static final int MAX_PAGE_TREE_ENTRIES     = 100_000;                                                                                                            
                                     }                                                                                                                                                                           
                                     ```                                                                                                                                                                         
                                2. In `PDFObjectStreamParser`:                                                                                                                                                   
                                   a. Constructor (after reading `numberOfObjects`):                                                                                                                             
                                      ```java                                                                                                                                                                    
                                      if (numberOfObjects > ParserConfig.MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS) {                                                                                                            
                                          throw new IOException("/N entry too large in object stream: " + numberOfObjects);                                                                                      
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                      ```                                                                                                                                                                        
                                   b. In `parseAllObjects()`:                                                                                                                                                    
                                      ```java                                                                                                                                                                    
                                      if (numberOfObjects > ParserConfig.MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS) {                                                                                                            
                                          throw new IOException("Refusing to parse too many objects: " + numberOfObjects);                                                                                       
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                      ```                                                                                                                                                                        
                                   c. In `privateReadObjectNumbers()` (pseudocode; insert counter):                                                                                                              
                                      ```java                                                                                                                                                                    
                                      Map<Long,Integer> map = new HashMap<>();                                                                                                                                   
                                      int count = 0;                                                                                                                                                             
                                      while (/* reading pairs */) {                                                                                                                                              
                                          if (++count > ParserConfig.MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS) {                                                                                                                
                                              throw new IOException("Too many object numbers in object stream");                                                                                                 
                                          }                                                                                                                                                                      
                                          // existing logic...                                                                                                                                                   
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                      ```                                                                                                                                                                        
                                3. In `COSParser.checkPagesDictionary(...)`:                                                                                                                                     
                                   - At the start of the method (or inside the loop over `kidsList`):                                                                                                            
                                     ```java                                                                                                                                                                     
                                     if (set.size() > ParserConfig.MAX_PAGE_TREE_ENTRIES) {                                                                                                                      
                                         throw new IOException("Page tree exceeds maximum allowed entries");                                                                                                     
                                     }                                                                                                                                                                           
                                     ```                                                                                                                                                                         
                                   - This check enforces a global cap on nodes visited.                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Justification                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - Enforcing upper bounds on loops driven by potentially attacker-controlled headers (`/N`, page-tree depth) prevents runaway CPU usage, addressing libFuzzer                     
                             timeouts.                                                                                                                                                                           
                                - Thresholds are configurable constants, so they can be tuned for larger real-world PDFs without code redesign.                                                                  
                                - The existing parsing logic, cycle-detection, exception semantics, and downstream processing remain intact for valid inputs below thresholds.                                   
                                - No harness, test code, or external library is modified.                                                                                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             6. Potential Side Effects & Mitigations                                                                                                                                             
                                - Very large but legitimate PDFs with >100k compressed objects or >100k page nodes will now fail with an `IOException`. Mitigation: adjust `ParserConfig`                        
                             thresholds upward if needed, or expose configuration via system properties.                                                                                                         
                                - Existing unit tests should be reviewed to ensure no test PDF exceeds these counts; if so, raise thresholds only for tests or add an override.                                  
                                - Since these are fatal parse-time errors, they will be reported cleanly rather than causing silent hangs.                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             7. References to Similar Code                                                                                                                                                       
                                - Many parsers enforce caps (e.g., XML entity expansion limits, image dimension limits). This approach mirrors standard resource exhaustion defenses.                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             This strategy eliminates the root cause of the fuzzer timeoutsunbounded, fuzz-controlled loopswhile preserving normal functionality.                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===

                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Issue===                                                                                                                                                                         
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                             The initial issue reported a fuzzing harness timeout (`ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`) when exercising PDF parsing. A patch was attempted to add upperbound checks                     
                             (`MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS`, `MAX_PAGE_TREE_ENTRIES`) in PDFObjectStreamParser and COSParser to prevent resourceexhaustion loops. After applying the patch, the                   
                             build failed with numerous Java compilation errors (illegal start of type, unmatched braces, try without catch/finally, reached end of file while parsing),                       
                             indicating malformed insertions and unbalanced class/method definitions.                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Initial Issue                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - A libFuzzer run against PDFBox hung or timed out, suggesting that certain PDF parsing routines could enter long or infinite loops (e.g., processing extremely                  
                             large `/N` values in object streams or very deep page trees).                                                                                                                       
                                - No stack traces or crash dumps were providedonly the timeout message from the fuzzer harness.                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Important Observations                                                                                                                                                           
                                - The timeout implies a performance or unboundedloop issue rather than a memory corruption crash.                                                                               
                                - The fuzzer likely drove numeric entries in PDF streams/pages to very large values, triggering heavy work or stuck loops in parsing logic.                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Patch Attempt                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - In PDFObjectStreamParser.java:                                                                                                                                                 
                                   Introduced `MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS = 100_000`.                                                                                                                            
                                   Checked `stream.getInt(COSName.N)` against that cap in the constructor and again before parseAllObjects().                                                                   
                                   Added a new helper method `privateReadObjectNumbers()` to replace inloop offset reading, with its own count guard.                                                          
                                - In COSParser.java:                                                                                                                                                             
                                   Declared `MAX_PAGE_TREE_ENTRIES = 100_000` at class scope.                                                                                                                   
                                   Modified `checkPagesDictionary()` to throw if the `set.size()` of visited page nodes exceeds the cap.                                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Patch Result and Logs                                                                                                                                                            
                                - The build aborted with ~69 errors, including:                                                                                                                                  
                                   illegal start of type and identifier expected at the very beginning of COSParser.java around the inserted constant declarations.                                         
                                   reached end of file while parsing indicating missing closing braces.                                                                                                       
                                   In PDFObjectStreamParser.java: try without catch/finally and illegal start of expression around the newly inserted helper method.                                        
                                - These errors point to misaligned hunk context: insertions landed outside of class/method bodies or broke existing braces/structure.                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Areas for Further Investigation                                                                                                                                                  
                                - Verify patch hunk alignment against current file versions, ensuring imports, class declarations, and method bodies remain syntactically correct.                               
                                - Inspect PDFObjectStreamParser.java around lines 144160 to confirm the new helper method is placed inside the class but outside other methods.                                 
                                - Inspect COSParser.java around the top of the class (imports and class declaration) to ensure the new constant is declared within the class body, not before it                 
                             or midimport section.                                                                                                                                                              
                                - Review matching pairs of braces (`{`/`}`) in both files to restore proper nesting of classes and methods.                                                                      
                                - Examine parseAllObjects() and checkPagesDictionary() contexts to confirm the new prechecks are inserted without overriding existing control flow or leaving                   
                             dangling code.                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                                                                                                
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                                                                                                                      
                             <issue>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </issue>

                             - All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous patches if needed.
