                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFObjectStreamParser.java:100-200                                                                                                 
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             100:                if (streamObject != null)                                                                                                                                       
                             101:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             102:                    streamObject.setDirect(false);                                                                                                                              
                             103:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             104:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             105:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             106:        finally                                                                                                                                                                 
                             107:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             108:            source.close();                                                                                                                                                     
                             109:            document = null;                                                                                                                                                    
                             110:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             111:        return streamObject;                                                                                                                                                    
                             112:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             113:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             114:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             115:     * Parse all compressed objects. The stream is closed after parsing.                                                                                                        
                             116:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             117:     * @return a map containing all parsed objects using the object number as key                                                                                               
                             118:     * @throws IOException if there is an error while parsing the stream                                                                                                        
                             119:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             120:    public Map<COSObjectKey, COSBase> parseAllObjects() throws IOException                                                                                                      
                             121:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             122:        Map<COSObjectKey, COSBase> allObjects = new HashMap<>();                                                                                                                
                             123:        try                                                                                                                                                                     
                             124:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             125:            Map<Integer, Long> objectNumbers = privateReadObjectOffsets();                                                                                                      
                             126:            // count the number of object numbers eliminating double entries                                                                                                    
                             127:            long numberOfObjNumbers = objectNumbers.values().stream().distinct().count();                                                                                       
                             128:            // the usage of the index should be restricted to cases where more than one                                                                                         
                             129:            // object use the same object number.                                                                                                                               
                             130:            // there are malformed pdfs in the wild which would lead to false results if                                                                                        
                             131:            // pdfbox always relies on the index if available. In most cases the object number                                                                                  
                             132:            // is sufficient to choose the correct object                                                                                                                       
                             133:            boolean indexNeeded = objectNumbers.size() > numberOfObjNumbers;                                                                                                    
                             134:            long currentPosition = source.getPosition();                                                                                                                        
                             135:            if (firstObject > 0 && currentPosition < firstObject)                                                                                                               
                             136:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             137:                source.skip(firstObject - (int) currentPosition);                                                                                                               
                             138:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             139:            int index = 0;                                                                                                                                                      
                             140:            for (Entry<Integer, Long> entry : objectNumbers.entrySet())                                                                                                         
                             141:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             142:                COSObjectKey objectKey = getObjectKey(entry.getValue(), 0);                                                                                                     
                             143:                // skip object if the index doesn't match                                                                                                                       
                             144:                if (indexNeeded && objectKey.getStreamIndex() > -1                                                                                                              
                             145:                        && objectKey.getStreamIndex() != index)                                                                                                                 
                             146:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             147:                    index++;                                                                                                                                                    
                             148:                    continue;                                                                                                                                                   
                             149:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             150:                int finalPosition = firstObject + entry.getKey();                                                                                                               
                             151:                currentPosition = source.getPosition();                                                                                                                         
                             152:                if (finalPosition > 0 && currentPosition < finalPosition)                                                                                                       
                             153:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             154:                    // jump to the offset of the object to be parsed                                                                                                            
                             155:                    source.skip(finalPosition - (int) currentPosition);                                                                                                         
                             156:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             157:                COSBase streamObject = parseDirObject();                                                                                                                        
                             158:                if (streamObject != null)                                                                                                                                       
                             159:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             160:                    streamObject.setDirect(false);                                                                                                                              
                             161:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             162:                allObjects.put(objectKey, streamObject);                                                                                                                        
                             163:                index++;                                                                                                                                                        
                             164:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             165:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             166:        finally                                                                                                                                                                 
                             167:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             168:            source.close();                                                                                                                                                     
                             169:            document = null;                                                                                                                                                    
                             170:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             171:        return allObjects;                                                                                                                                                      
                             172:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             173:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             174:    private Map<Long, Integer> privateReadObjectNumbers() throws IOException                                                                                                    
                             175:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             176:        // don't initialize map using numberOfObjects as there might by less object numbers than expected                                                                       
                             177:        Map<Long, Integer> objectNumbers = new HashMap<>();                                                                                                                     
                             178:        long firstObjectPosition = source.getPosition() + firstObject - 1;                                                                                                      
                             179:        for (int i = 0; i < numberOfObjects; i++)                                                                                                                               
                             180:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             181:            // don't read beyond the part of the stream reserved for the object numbers                                                                                         
                             182:            if (source.getPosition() >= firstObjectPosition)                                                                                                                    
                             183:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             184:                break;                                                                                                                                                          
                             185:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             186:            long objectNumber = readObjectNumber();                                                                                                                             
                             187:            int offset = (int) readLong();                                                                                                                                      
                             188:            objectNumbers.put(objectNumber, offset);                                                                                                                            
                             189:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             190:        return objectNumbers;                                                                                                                                                   
                             191:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             192:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             193:    private Map<Integer, Long> privateReadObjectOffsets() throws IOException                                                                                                    
                             194:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             195:        // according to the pdf spec the offsets shall be sorted ascending                                                                                                      
                             196:        // but we can't rely on that, so that we have to sort the offsets                                                                                                       
                             197:        // as the sequential parsers relies on it, see PDFBOX-4927                                                                                                              
                             198:        Map<Integer, Long> objectOffsets = new TreeMap<>();                                                                                                                     
                             199:        long firstObjectPosition = source.getPosition() + firstObject - 1;                                                                                                      
                             200:        for (int i = 0; i < numberOfObjects; i++)                                                                                                                               
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>

                             30:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             31:/**                                                                                                                                                                              
                             32: * This will parse a PDF 1.5 object stream and extract the object with given object number from the stream.                                                                      
                             33: *                                                                                                                                                                               
                             34: * @author Ben Litchfield                                                                                                                                                        
                             35: *                                                                                                                                                                               
                             36: */                                                                                                                                                                              
                             37:public class PDFObjectStreamParser extends BaseParser                                                                                                                            
                             38:{                                                                                                                                                                                
                             39:    private final int numberOfObjects;                                                                                                                                           
                             40:    private final int firstObject;                                                                                                                                               
                             41:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             42:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             43:     * Constructor.                                                                                                                                                              
                             44:     *                                                                                                                                                                           
                             45:     * @param stream The stream to parse.                                                                                                                                        
                             46:     * @param document The document for the current parsing.                                                                                                                     
                             47:     * @throws IOException If there is an error initializing the stream.                                                                                                         
                             48:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             49:    public PDFObjectStreamParser(COSStream stream, COSDocument document) throws IOException                                                                                      
                             50:    {                                                                                                                                                                            
                             51:        super(stream.createView());                                                                                                                                              
                             52:        this.document = document;                                                                                                                                                
                             53:        // get mandatory number of objects                                                                                                                                       
                             54:        numberOfObjects = stream.getInt(COSName.N);                                                                                                                              
                             55:        if (numberOfObjects == -1)                                                                                                                                               
                             56:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             57:            throw new IOException("/N entry missing in object stream");                                                                                                          
                             58:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             59:        if (numberOfObjects < 0)                                                                                                                                                 
                             60:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             61:            throw new IOException("Illegal /N entry in object stream: " + numberOfObjects);                                                                                      
                             62:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             63:        // get mandatory stream offset of the first object                                                                                                                       
                             64:        firstObject = stream.getInt(COSName.FIRST);                                                                                                                              
                             65:        if (firstObject == -1)                                                                                                                                                   
                             66:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             67:            throw new IOException("/First entry missing in object stream");                                                                                                      
                             68:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             69:        if (firstObject < 0)                                                                                                                                                     
                             70:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             71:            throw new IOException("Illegal /First entry in object stream: " + firstObject);                                                                                      
                             72:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             73:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             ```

                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Issue===                                                                                                                                                                         
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             The initial issue is that libFuzzer reports a timeout when exercising the PDFBox parser. An attempt was made to defend against resource exhaustion by capping two                   
                             quantities: the number of objects in an object stream and the number of entries in a page tree. The patch introduces `MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS` (100 000) in                       
                             `PDFObjectStreamParser` and `MAX_PAGE_TREE_ENTRIES` (100 000) in `COSParser`. After applying the patch, the fuzzing run still ends with `ERROR: libFuzzer:                          
                             timeout`, indicating the timeout persists.                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Initial Issue                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - The only symptom logged by libFuzzer is `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`.                                                                                                           
                                - No stack trace or exception is produced; the parser appears to hang or run too long on some inputs.                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Observations from the Issue                                                                                                                                                      
                                - The timeout suggests a potential infinite or extremely long loop, likely driven by large count values in the parsed PDF structures.                                            
                                - Two code regions are prime suspects for unbounded loops:                                                                                                                       
                                   Object-stream parsing (iterating over `/N` entries).                                                                                                                         
                                   Page-tree traversal (recursing through `/Kids` arrays).                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Patch Attempt                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - In `PDFObjectStreamParser.java`:                                                                                                                                               
                                   Introduced                                                                                                                                                                   
                                    private static final int MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS = 100_000;                                                                                                                
                                   After reading `numberOfObjects = stream.getInt(COSName.N)`, added:                                                                                                           
                                      if (numberOfObjects > MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS) {                                                                                                                         
                                          throw new IOException("Object stream /N value too large: " + numberOfObjects);                                                                                         
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                   In `parseAllObjects()`, before parsing loop, re-checks `numberOfObjects` against the same cap and throws if exceeded.                                                        
                                - In `COSParser.java`:                                                                                                                                                           
                                   Introduced                                                                                                                                                                   
                                    private static final int MAX_PAGE_TREE_ENTRIES = 100_000;                                                                                                                    
                                   In the private method `checkPagesDictionary(COSDictionary, Set<COSObject>)`, before recursing or iterating, added:                                                           
                                      if (set.size() > MAX_PAGE_TREE_ENTRIES) {                                                                                                                                  
                                          throw new IOException("Page tree exceeds maximum allowed entries: " + set.size());                                                                                     
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Result After Applying Patch                                                                                                                                                      
                                - The fuzzer run still times out without any new logging or exceptions.                                                                                                          
                                - The patch did not unblock the hanging code path.                                                                                                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Areas for Further Investigation                                                                                                                                                  
                                - PDFObjectStreamParser: loops that consume or skip object-data beyond just counting objects  examine offset lists and token scanning.                                          
                                - COSParser page-tree logic: check other recursive paths (e.g., indirect references, malformed dictionaries).                                                                    
                                - Cross-reference table parsing and stream decoding loops (e.g., `readXrefStream`, `parseXrefTable`) for large or malicious values.                                              
                                - Tokenization and scanning methods invoked by the harness, to see whether they properly bail out on malformed or deeply nested data.                                            
                                - Any other unbounded loops driven by stream lengths (`Length` entry), filters, or content streams.                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                                                                                                
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                                                                                                                      
                             <issue>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </issue>                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Additional Issue Log                                                                                                                                                             
                             Here is the additional issue log after the last patch attempt:                                                                                                                      
                             <additional_issue>                                                                                                                                                                  
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </additional_issue>                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Notes                                                                                                                                                                            
                             - All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous patches if needed.                                                                               
                             - If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a single patch attempt.                                                                              
                             - Try different approaches to resolve the issues.                                                                                                                                   
                             ===Analysis Report===

                             627:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             628:            catch (NumberFormatException exception)                                                                                                                             
                             629:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             630:                LOG.warn("XRefTable: invalid number of objects: {}", currentLine);                                                                                              
                             631:                return false;                                                                                                                                                   
                             632:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             633:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             634:            parser.skipSpaces();                                                                                                                                                
                             635:            for(int i = 0; i < count; i++)                                                                                                                                      
                             636:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             637:                if (parser.isEOF() )                                                                                                                                            
                             638:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             639:                    break;                                                                                                                                                      
                             640:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             641:                int nextChar = source.peek();                                                                                                                                   
                             642:                if (nextChar == 't' || BaseParser.isEndOfName(nextChar))                                                                                                        
                             643:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             644:                    break;                                                                                                                                                      
                             645:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             646:                //Ignore table contents                                                                                                                                         
                             647:                currentLine = parser.readLine();                                                                                                                                
                             648:                splitString = currentLine.split("\\s");                                                                                                                         
                             649:                if (splitString.length < 3)                                                                                                                                     
                             650:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFXrefStreamParser.java:119-130                                                                                                   
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             119:    public void parse(XrefTrailerResolver resolver) throws IOException                                                                                                          
                             120:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             121:        byte[] currLine = new byte[w[0] + w[1] + w[2]];                                                                                                                         
                             122:        while (!source.isEOF() && objectNumbers.hasNext())                                                                                                                      
                             123:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             124:            readNextValue(currLine);                                                                                                                                            
                             125:            // get the current objID                                                                                                                                            
                             126:            long objID = objectNumbers.next();                                                                                                                                  
                             127:            // default value is 1 if w[0] == 0, otherwise parse first field                                                                                                     
                             128:            int type = w[0] == 0 ? 1 : (int) parseValue(currLine, 0, w[0]);                                                                                                     
                             129:            // Skip free objects (type 0) and invalid types                                                                                                                     
                             130:            if (type == 0)                                                                                                                                                      
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BaseParser.java:989-1000                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             989:            // This is not suppose to happen, but we will allow for it                                                                                                          
                             990:            // so we are more compatible with POS writers that don't                                                                                                            
                             991:            // follow the spec                                                                                                                                                  
                             992:            long startOffset = source.getPosition();                                                                                                                            
                             993:            String badString = readString();

                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Overview and Core Insights                                                                                                                                                       
                                - The persistent timeout indicates unbounded loops in the cross-reference (xref) parsing code, not only in object streams or page trees.                                         
                                - Two key loops remain uncontrolled:                                                                                                                                             
                                  a) XrefParser.parseXrefTable: an unbounded while(true) loop and nested for-loop driven by a maliciously large count from the PDF.                                            
                                  b) PDFXrefStreamParser.parse: iterates over an Iterator (objectNumbers) built from the /Index array, which can be arbitrarily large.                                           
                                - Existing caps in PDFObjectStreamParser and COSParser address object streams and page trees but do not impact xref table or xref stream parsing.                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Preserve Existing Logic                                                                                                                                                          
                                - Keep all prior patches to PDFObjectStreamParser and COSParser as they protect against their respective resource exhaustion paths.                                              
                                - Maintain the tolerance for malformed but benign PDFs (e.g., defaulting /Index when absent, warnings rather than hard failures in non-security code).                           
                                - Do not alter fuzz harness or tests.                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Patch Plan                                                                                                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                A. XrefParser caps                                                                                                                                                               
                                - Introduce in XrefParser.java:                                                                                                                                                  
                                    private static final int MAX_XREF_TABLE_ENTRIES = 100_000;                                                                                                                   
                                - At the start of parseXrefTable(), declare and initialize:                                                                                                                      
                                    int accumulatedEntries = 0;                                                                                                                                                  
                                - After reading and parsing count (line 623630), insert:                                                                                                                      
                                    if (count < 0 || count > MAX_XREF_TABLE_ENTRIES                                                                                                                              
                                        || (long)accumulatedEntries + count > MAX_XREF_TABLE_ENTRIES) {                                                                                                          
                                        throw new IOException("Xref table section too large: count=" + count);                                                                                                   
                                    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                                    accumulatedEntries += count;                                                                                                                                                 
                                - This ensures:                                                                                                                                                                  
                                     No single section exceeds the cap.                                                                                                                                         
                                     Total entries across all sections cannot grow unbounded.                                                                                                                   
                                - Leave the rest of the while(true)/for loops intact so normal PDFs still parse correctly.                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                B. PDFXrefStreamParser caps                                                                                                                                                      
                                - In PDFXrefStreamParser.java, add:                                                                                                                                              
                                    private static final int MAX_XREF_STREAM_ENTRIES = 100_000;                                                                                                                  
                                - Locate where objectNumbers is built (typically in constructor or initialize method). Before iterating:                                                                         
                                     Compute expectedEntries by summing counts from the /Index array (or default count).                                                                                        
                                      For example:                                                                                                                                                               
                                        long expectedEntries = 0;                                                                                                                                                
                                        COSArray index = stream.getCOSArray(COSName.INDEX);                                                                                                                      
                                        if (index != null) {                                                                                                                                                     
                                          for (int i = 0; i < index.size(); i += 2) {                                                                                                                            
                                            long objCount = index.get(i+1).toLong();                                                                                                                             
                                            expectedEntries += objCount;                                                                                                                                         
                                            if (expectedEntries > MAX_XREF_STREAM_ENTRIES) {                                                                                                                     
                                                throw new IOException("XRef stream /Index too large: total=" + expectedEntries);                                                                                 
                                            }                                                                                                                                                                    
                                          }                                                                                                                                                                      
                                        } else {                                                                                                                                                                 
                                          // default single section: numberOfEntries = maximum object number from header                                                                                         
                                          expectedEntries = trailer.getSize(); // as per spec                                                                                                                    
                                          if (expectedEntries > MAX_XREF_STREAM_ENTRIES) {                                                                                                                       
                                              throw new IOException("XRef stream default entries too large: " + expectedEntries);                                                                                
                                          }                                                                                                                                                                      
                                        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                                     Only after this check, build objectNumbers list and proceed.                                                                                                               
                                - Alternatively, if objectNumbers is pre-built and no easy way to get counts ahead of time, in parse():                                                                          
                                    int processed = 0;                                                                                                                                                           
                                    while (!source.isEOF() && objectNumbers.hasNext()) {                                                                                                                         
                                        if (++processed > MAX_XREF_STREAM_ENTRIES) {                                                                                                                             
                                            throw new IOException("Too many XRef stream entries: " + processed);                                                                                                 
                                        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                                        ...                                                                                                                                                                      
                                    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Reapply Previous Patches                                                                                                                                                         
                                - Ensure the constants and exception checks in PDFObjectStreamParser (MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_OBJECTS) and COSParser (MAX_PAGE_TREE_ENTRIES) remain in place.                          
                                - No need to modify or remove those previous defenses.                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Justification                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - By capping xref-related loops, we eliminate the ability of a malicious PDF to drive parseXrefTable or parse XRef streams into extremely long loops, thus                       
                             preventing libFuzzer timeouts.                                                                                                                                                      
                                - Thresholds (100 000 entries) mirror existing caps in object streams and page trees, providing consistent resource limits.                                                      
                                - Throwing IOException cleanly aborts parsing this document without impacting other code paths.                                                                                  
                                - Existing valid PDFs with reasonable xref tables/streams remain unaffected.                                                                                                     
                                - No harness, fuzz flags, or tests are modified; this preserves all existing test coverage and fuzzing entry points.                                                             
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             6. Potential Side Effects & Mitigations                                                                                                                                             
                                - Side Effect: Very large but legitimate PDFs with >100 000 xref entries would be rejected. Mitigation: If this is unacceptable, raise the cap or make it                        
                             configurable via a system property, with a safe default.                                                                                                                            
                                - Ensure all thrown IOExceptions are handled upstream to abort parsing gracefully and release resources.                                                                         
                                - Add unit tests to verify that too-large xref tables/streams produce an IOException with a clear message.                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             7. Summary of Changes                                                                                                                                                               
                                - XrefParser.java: add MAX_XREF_TABLE_ENTRIES, accumulatedEntries, throw on oversized sections/total.                                                                            
                                - PDFXrefStreamParser.java: add MAX_XREF_STREAM_ENTRIES, pre-scan /Index array (or per-iteration counter), throw on oversized.                                                   
                                - Retain and reapply previous patches in PDFObjectStreamParser and COSParser unchanged.                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===
